narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Covers a lot of topics in industrial organization, lectures are extremely helpful in understanding papers and key concepts Weaknesses: None

Strengths: students learn about the key methods and questions developed in the field. The homework assignments are extremely helpful in guiding the student through the methods and implementation details. Both professors are effective communicators. weakness: I believe students would benefit if professors could provide more feedback on the homework assignments. For instance, the professors could briefly tell the students what was clearly wrong and what could have fixed it. Maybe the instructors could provide some sort of solution document, containing the main issues students were expected to confront while implementing the assignment.
It's weird to learn dynamic models before the static ones, although the schedule may work better for the professors.
The course is well-organized but maybe it could add more topics in IO.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. A must take for students not only interested in industrial organization but also in trade, spatial economics, macro, applied micro
Yes, if you want to learn solid structural IO.
Yes. It provides great knowledge and insights for those who are interested in IO.
